  "text": "Phenolic compounds are synthesized by plants as an adaptation to biotic and abiotic stress conditions. Their levels vary widely during growth and maturation, which are affected by agricultural practices, and they contribute to pungency, bitterness, flavor, and color [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
